data.database_description: The database is designed to manage and organize documents along with their associated metadata within an organization. It supports roles and user authentication by linking users to specific roles, and it allows for categorization of documents through structures and functional areas, facilitating organized access and retrieval. The database also manages sections and images linked to documents, enabling detailed content breakdowns and visual representations. Overall, this schema is structured to efficiently handle document management processes, ensuring that documents are accessible, categorized, and visually enriched within a defined organizational framework.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each role.
Descriptive name or title of the role.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Defines roles within an organization, linking users to specific responsibilities.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each user.
Links the user to their respective role, ensuring role-based access control.
Full name of the user.
Login identifier for the user, potentially used as a username or email.
Hashed password for user authentication.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Manages user authentication and links users to specific roles within the organization.

columns.columnDescription: Primary key representing a unique identifier for each document structure.
References the parent structure code to establish hierarchical relationships between sections.
Provides a textual description of the document structure section.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Manages hierarchical categorization of document sections within an organization.

columns.columnDescription: Primary key identifying each unique functional area.
Identifier for hierarchical structuring, linking to a parent functional area if applicable.
Description providing details about the specific functional area.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Defines and categorizes various functional areas within the organization.

columns.columnDescription: Primary key uniquely identifying an image.
Provides descriptive text for the image, enhancing accessibility.
Specifies a name for the image file or identifier.
Contains the URL where the image can be accessed online.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores metadata and references for images used within documents, providing alternative text, name, and URL.

columns.columnDescription: Primary key representing a unique identifier for each document.
References the document structure code to categorize documents within their respective sections.
Indicates the type of document, such as Book or Paper.
Tracks how many times a document has been accessed or retrieved.
Provides the name or title of the document.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about documents, including their metadata and categorization.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier linking the document to its metadata.
Identifier linking the document to a specific functional area.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Associates documents with their respective functional areas for categorization.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each document section.
Identifier linking the section to its corresponding document.
Order of the section within a document, indicating its position.
Code representing the type or category of the section.
Title describing the content or purpose of the section.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores sections of documents, including their sequence and titles for organized content breakdown.

columns.columnDescription: Primary key that uniquely identifies a section within a document.
Foreign key linking to an image, associating the image with a specific document section.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Links document sections to images, facilitating a relationship between document content and visual representation.
